    "plan_content": "Here's the full plan for the `ollama rename` feature. It touches exactly **4 files** and reuses only existing helpers — no new utilities needed.\n\n---\n\n## What gets added\n\n### `api/types.go` — New `RenameRequest` struct\nAfter `CopyRequest` (line 765). Identical shape — `Source` + `Destination` string fields with the same JSON tags.\n\n### `api/client.go` — New `Rename()` method\nAfter `Copy()` (line 387). POST to `/api/rename`, no response body. Follows the exact same pattern as `Copy()`.\n\n### `server/routes.go` — New `RenameHandler` + route registration\n- Route: `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` added next to `/api/copy` (line ~1698).\n- Handler (after `CopyHandler`, line 1483) does these steps in order:\n  1. Bind JSON → 400 on bad input\n  2. `model.ParseName` + `.IsValid()` + `getExistingName()` for source → 400 if invalid\n  3. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if `os.ErrNotExist` (captures the manifest object for later deletion)\n  4. Same name parsing for destination → 400 if invalid\n  5. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` — if this succeeds (no error) → **409 Conflict**\n  6. `CopyModel(src, dst)` — copies the manifest file\n  7. `srcManifest.Remove()` + `srcManifest.RemoveLayers()` — deletes the source\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` — CLI `RenameHandler` + `renameCmd` cobra command\n- `RenameHandler` func (after `CopyHandler`, line 1350): calls `client.Rename()`, prints `\"renamed 'X' to 'Y'\\n\"`\n- `renameCmd` cobra command (after `copyCmd`, line 2263): `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n- Wired into the env-docs loop slice and `rootCmd.AddCommand()`\n\n---\n\n## HTTP error map\n\n| Condition | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Missing/invalid JSON | 400 |\n| Invalid source/destination name | 400 |\n| Source not found | **404** |\n| Destination already exists | **409** |\n| Filesystem error | 500 |\n| Success | 200 (empty body) |",
